  ],
  "text": "Chromium's renderer process sandbox implementation consists of four key components: (1) BaselinePolicy in sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf-helpers/baseline_policy.cc implements the seccomp-BPF baseline policy for Linux sandboxing, providing foundational system call filtering rules. (2) PolicyBase in sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy_base.cc is the concrete Windows implementation of TargetPolicy, configuring sandbox policies and process initialization on Windows platforms. (3) RendererProcessPolicy in sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_renderer_policy_linux.cc implements BPF policies specific to renderer processes on Linux, with the EvaluateSyscall method evaluating individual system calls to determine if they should be allowed or restricted. (4) SandboxType enum in sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h declares sandbox type utilities and the enumeration that maps different process types (renderer, GPU, utility, etc.) to their corresponding sandbox configurations. These components form the core security architecture for isolating Chromium's renderer processes from the kernel and limiting their attack surface."
}

